This is a complete, professional-grade Tetris game contained within a single HTML file. I have used a **"Cyberpunk Neon"** aesthetic with glowing effects, smooth animations, and a polished user interface.

Save the code below as an `.html` file (e.g., `tetris.html`) and open it in any modern web browser.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>NEON TETRIS</title>
    <style>
        :root {
            --bg-color: #0a0a12;
            --panel-color: #161625;
            --accent-color: #00f2ff;
            --text-color: #ffffff;
            --font-main: 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
        }

        * {
            box-sizing: border-box;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
        }

        body {
            background-color: var(--bg-color);
            color: var(--text-color);
            font-family: var(--font-main);
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            min-height: 100vh;
            overflow: hidden;
        }

        #game-container {
            position: relative;
            display: flex;
            gap: 20px;
            padding: 20px;
            background: var(--panel-color);
            border-radius: 15px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 40px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5), 0 0 20px rgba(0, 242, 255, 0.1);
            border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
        }

        canvas {
            display: block;
            background-color: #000;
            border-radius: 4px;
            box-shadow: inset 0 0 10px rgba(0,0,0,1);
        }

        #main-board {
            border: 2px solid #333;
        }

        .side-panel {
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            justify-content: space-between;
            width: 150px;
        }

        .stat-box {
            background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
            padding: 15px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
            text-align: center;
            border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
        }

        .stat-label {
            font-size: 0.8rem;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 2px;
            color: var(--accent-color);
            margin-bottom: 5px;
        }

        .stat-value {
            font-size: 1.5rem;
            font-weight: bold;
            font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
        }

        #next-piece-canvas {
            background: #000;
            border-radius: 4px;
            margin-top: 10px;
        }

        .controls-hint {
            font-size: 0.7rem;
            color: #666;
            line-height: 1.6;
            text-align: center;
        }

        /* Overlays */
        #overlay {
            position: absolute;
            top: 0;
            left: 0;
            width: 100%;
            height: 100%;
            background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8);
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            z-index: 10;
            border-radius: 15px;
            transition: opacity 0.3s ease;
        }

        h1 {
            font-size: 2.5rem;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            letter-spacing: 5px;
            text-shadow: 0 0 15px var(--accent-color);
        }

        button {
            padding: 12px 30px;
            font-size: 1.2rem;
            background: transparent;
            color: var(--accent-color);
            border: 2px solid var(--accent-color);
            border-radius: 5px;
            cursor: pointer;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 2px;
            transition: all 0.2s ease;
        }

        button:hover {
            background: var(--accent-color);
            color: #000;
            box-shadow: 0 0 20px var(--accent-color);
        }

        .hidden {
            display: none !important;
        }

        /* Glow effect for title */
        .title-glow {
            animation: glow 2s ease-in-out infinite alternate;
        }

        @keyframes glow {
            from { text-shadow: 0 0 10px var(--accent-color); }
            to { text-shadow: 0 0 30px var(--accent-color), 0 0 10px #fff; }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <div id="game-container">
        <!-- Main Game Board -->
        <canvas id="main-board" width="300" height="600"></canvas>

        <!-- Side Panel -->
        <div class="side-panel">
            <div>
                <div class="stat-box">
                    <div class="stat-label">Next</div>
                    <canvas id="next-piece-canvas" width="100" height="100"></canvas>
                </div>

                <div class="stat-box">
                    <div class="stat-label">Score</div>
                    <div id="score" class="stat-value">0</div>
                </div>

                <div class="stat-box">
                    <div class="stat-label">Level</div>
                    <div id="level" class="stat-value">1</div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="controls-hint">
                ← → : Move<br>
                ↑ : Rotate<br>
                ↓ : Soft Drop<br>
                SPACE : Hard Drop
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Start/Game Over Overlay -->
        <div id="overlay">
            <h1 class="title-glow" id="overlay-title">TETRIS</h1>
            <button id="start-btn">Start Game</button>
        </div>
    </div>

    <script>
        /** 
         * GAME CONFIGURATION & CONSTANTS
         */
        const COLS = 10;
        const ROWS = 20;
        const BLOCK_SIZE = 30;

        const COLORS = [
            null,
            '#FF0D72', // T - Pink
            '#0DC2FF', // I - Cyan
            '#0DFF72', // S - Green
            '#F538FF', // Z - Purple
            '#FF8E0D', // L - Orange
            '#FFE138', // O - Yellow
            '#3877FF', // J - Blue
        ];

        const SHAPES = [
            null,
            [[0, 1, 0], [1, 1, 1], [0, 0, 0]], // T
            [[0, 2, 0, 0], [0, 2, 0, 0], [0, 2, 0, 0], [0, 2, 0, 0]], // I
            [[0, 3, 3], [3, 3, 0], [0, 0, 0]], // S
            [[4, 4, 0], [0, 4, 4], [0, 0, 0]], // Z
            [[5, 0, 0], [5, 5, 5], [0, 0, 0]], // L
            [[6, 6], [6, 6]], // O
            [[0, 0, 7], [7, 7, 7], [0, 0, 0]], // J
        ];

        /**
         * GAME STATE
         */
        const canvas = document.getElementById('main-board');
        const ctx = canvas.getContext('2d');
        const nextCanvas = document.getElementById('next-piece-canvas');
        const nextCtx = nextCanvas.getContext('2d');

        let board = createMatrix(COLS, ROWS);
        let score = 0;
        let level = 1;
        let linesCleared = 0;
        let dropCounter = 0;
        let dropInterval = 1000;
        let lastTime = 0;

        let player = {
            pos: {x: 0, y: 0},
            matrix: null,
            next: null,
            colorId: 0
        };

        /**
         * CORE LOGIC
         */

        function createMatrix(w, h) {
            const matrix = [];
            while (h--) {
                matrix.push(new Array(w).fill(0));
            }
            return matrix;
        }

        // Draw a single block with a "neon" look
        function drawBlock(context, x, y, colorId, isGhost = false) {
            const color = COLORS[colorId];
            const px = x * BLOCK_SIZE;
            const py = y * BLOCK_SIZE;

            if (isGhost) {
                context.strokeStyle = color;
                context.lineWidth = 2;
                context.strokeRect(px + 2, py + 2, BLOCK_SIZE - 4, BLOCK_SIZE - 4);
                return;
            }

            // Main block body
            context.fillStyle = color;
            context.fillRect(px + 1, py + 1, BLOCK_SIZE - 2, BLOCK_SIZE - 2);

            // Highlight (Top-left shine)
            context.fillStyle = 'rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3)';
            context.fillRect(px + 3, py + 3, BLOCK_SIZE - 10, 4);

            // Shine (Bottom-right)
            context.fillStyle = 'rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2)';
            context.fillRect(px + 3, py + BLOCK_SIZE - 7, BLOCK_SIZE - 10, 4);

            // Glow effect
            context.shadowBlur = 10;
            context.shadowColor = color;
        }

        function draw() {
            // Clear board
            ctx.fillStyle = '#000';
            ctx.shadowBlur = 0; // Reset shadow for background
            ctx.fillRect(0, 0, canvas.width, canvas.height);

            // Draw grid lines (subtle)
            ctx.strokeStyle = 'rgba(255,255,255,0.03)';
            ctx.lineWidth = 1;
            for(let i=0; i<=COLS; i++) {
                ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(i*BLOCK_SIZE, 0); ctx.lineTo(i*BLOCK_SIZE, canvas.height); ctx.stroke();
            }
            for(let i=0; i<=ROWS; i++) {
                ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(0, i*BLOCK_SIZE); ctx.lineTo(canvas.width, i*BLOCK_SIZE); ctx.stroke();
            }

            drawMatrix(board, {x: 0, y: 0}, ctx);
            drawGhost(); // Draw preview of where piece will land
            drawMatrix(player.matrix, player.pos, ctx);
        }

        function drawNext() {
            nextCtx.fillStyle = '#000';
            nextCtx.shadowBlur = 0;
            nextCtx.fillRect(0, 0, nextCanvas.width, nextCanvas.height);

            // Center the preview piece
            const m = player.next;
            const size = 20; // smaller for preview
            const offsetX = (nextCanvas.width - m[0].length * size) / 2;
            const offsetY = (nextCanvas.height - m.length * size) / 2;

            for (let y = 0; y < m.length; ++y) {
                for (let x = 0; x < m[y].length; ++x) {
                    if (m[y][x] !== 0) {
                        const colorId = m[y][x];
                        nextCtx.fillStyle = COLORS[colorId];
                        nextCtx.shadowBlur = 5;
                        nextCtx.shadowColor = COLORS[colorId];
                        nextCtx.fillRect(offsetX + x * size, offsetY + y * size, size - 1, size - 1);
                    }
                }
            }
        }

        function drawMatrix(matrix, offset, context) {
            matrix.forEach((row, y) => {
                row.forEach((value, x) => {
                    if (value !== 0) {
                        drawBlock(context, x + offset.x, y + offset.y, value);
                    }
                });
            });
        }

        // Ghost piece calculation
        function drawGhost() {
            const ghostPos = { x: player.pos.x, y: player.pos.y };
            while (!collide(board, { pos: ghostPos, matrix: player.matrix })) {
                ghostPos.y++;
            }
            ghostPos.y--; // step back to last valid position

            player.matrix.forEach((row, y) => {
                row.forEach((value, x) => {
                    if (value !== 0) {
                        const px = (x + ghostPos.x) * BLOCK_SIZE;
                        const py = (y + ghostPos.y) * BLOCK_SIZE;
                        ctx.strokeStyle = COLORS[value];
                        ctx.lineWidth = 1;
                        ctx.strokeRect(px + 4, py + 4, BLOCK_SIZE - 8, BLOCK_SIZE - 8);
                    }
                });
            });
        }

        function collide(board, player) {
            const [m, o] = [player.matrix, player.pos];
            for (let y = 0; y < m.length; ++y) {
                for (let x = 0; x < m[y].length; ++x) {
                    if (m[y][x] !== 0 &&
                       (board[y + o.y] && board[y + o.y][x + o.x]) !== 0) {
                        return true;
                    }
                }
            }
            return false;
        }

        function merge(board, player) {
            player.matrix.forEach((row, y) => {
                row.forEach((value, x) => {
                    if (value !== 0) {
                        board[y + player.pos.y][x + player.pos.x] = value;
                    }
                });
            });
        }

        function rotate(matrix, dir) {
            for (let y = 0; y < matrix.length; ++y) {
                for (let x = 0; x < y; ++x) {
                    [
                        matrix[x][y],
                        matrix[y][x],
                    ] = [
                        matrix[y][x],
                        matrix[x][y],
                    ];
                }
            }
            if (dir > 0) {
                matrix.forEach(row => row.reverse());
            } else {
                matrix.reverse();
            }
        }

        function playerDrop() {
            player.pos.y++;
            if (collide(board, player)) {
                player.pos.y--;
                merge(board, player);
                playerReset();
                arenaSweep();
                updateScore();
            }
            dropCounter = 0;
        }

        function playerHardDrop() {
            while (!collide(board, player)) {
                player.pos.y++;
            }
            player.pos.y--;
            merge(board, player);
            playerReset();
            arenaSweep();
            updateScore();
            dropCounter = 0;
        }

        function playerMove(dir) {
            player.pos.x += dir;
            if (collide(board, player)) {
                player.pos.x -= dir;
            }
        }

        function playerRotate(dir) {
            const pos = player.pos.x;
            let offset = 1;
            rotate(player.matrix, dir);
            while (collide(board, player)) {
                player.pos.x += offset;
                offset = -(offset + (offset > 0 ? 1 : -1));
                if (offset > player.matrix[0].length) {
                    rotate(player.matrix, -dir);
                    player.pos.x = pos;
                    return;
                }
            }
        }

        function playerReset() {
            if (!player.next) {
                player.next = SHAPES[Math.floor(Math.random() * (SHAPES.length - 1)) + 1];
            }
            
            player.matrix = player.next;
            player.next = SHAPES[Math.floor(Math.random() * (SHAPES.length - 1)) + 1];
            
            player.pos.y = 0;
            player.pos.x = (board[0].length / 2 | 0) -
                           (player.matrix[0].length / 2 | 0);

            if (collide(board, player)) {
                // GAME OVER
                gameOver();
            }
            drawNext();
        }

        function arenaSweep() {
            let rowCount = 1;
            outer: for (let y = board.length - 1; y > 0; --y) {
                for (let x = 0; x < board[y].length; ++x) {
                    if (board[y][x] === 0) {
                        continue outer;
                    }
                }

                // Row is full
                const row = board.splice(y, 1)[0].fill(0);
                board.unshift(row);
                ++y;

                score += rowCount * 100;
                rowCount *= 2;
                linesCleared++;

                if (linesCleared % 10 === 0) {
                    level++;
                    dropInterval = Math.max(100, 1000 - (level * 80));
                }
            }
        }

        function updateScore() {
            document.getElementById('score').innerText = score;
            document.getElementById('level').innerText = level;
        }

        /**
         * GAME LOOP & CONTROL
         */

        let isPaused = true;

        function update(time = 0) {
            if (isPaused) return;

            const deltaTime = time - lastTime;
            lastTime = time;

            dropCounter += deltaTime;
            if (dropCounter > dropInterval) {
                playerDrop();
            }

            draw();
            requestAnimationFrame(update);
        }

        function gameOver() {
            isPaused = true;
            document.getElementById('overlay-title').innerText = "GAME OVER";
            document.getElementById('start-btn').innerText = "Restart";
            document.getElementById('overlay').classList.remove('hidden');
        }

        function startGame() {
            // Reset State
            board = createMatrix(COLS, ROWS);
            score = 0;
            level = 1;
            linesCleared = 0;
            dropInterval = 1000;
            player.next = null;
            updateScore();

            document.getElementById('overlay').classList.add('hidden');
            isPaused = false;
            playerReset();
            lastTime = performance.now();
            update();
        }

        // Input Handling
        document.addEventListener('keydown', event => {
            if (isPaused) return;

            if (event.keyCode === 37) { // Left
                playerMove(-1);
            } else if (event.keyCode === 39) { // Right
                playerMove(1);
            } else if (event.keyCode === 40) { // Down
                playerDrop();
            } else if (event.keyCode === 38) { // Up (Rotate)
                playerRotate(1);
            } else if (event.keyCode === 32) { // Space (Hard Drop)
                playerHardDrop();
            }
        });

        document.getElementById('start-btn').addEventListener('click', startGame);

        // Initial Draw
        draw();

    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

### Key Features of this Implementation:

1.  **Visual Polish:** 
    *   **Neon Aesthetics:** Every block has a shadow glow, highlights, and subtle gradients to look "retro-future."
    *   **Ghost Piece:** Shows a hollow outline where the piece will land, which is essential for high-level play.
    *   **Animations:** Smooth transitions using `requestAnimationFrame`.
2.  **Gameplay Mechanics:**
    *   **Hard Drop:** Press `Space` to instantly lock a piece (essential for speed).
    *   **Soft Drop:** Press `Down Arrow` to fall faster.
    *   **Rotation System:** Includes basic "wall kick" logic so you can rotate near the edges without getting stuck.
    *   **Leveling System:** The game gets progressively faster every 10 lines cleared.
    *   **Next Piece Preview:** A dedicated side canvas shows you what's coming next.
3.  **Technical Details:**
    *   **Pure Vanilla JS/CSS:** No external libraries or images required. Everything is drawn programmatically on the `<canvas>`.
    *   **Responsive Logic:** The game uses a strict grid system, ensuring perfectly aligned movement and collisions.

### Controls:
*   **Left / Right Arrows:** Move Piece
*   **Up Arrow:** Rotate Piece
*   **Down Arrow:** Soft Drop (Move faster)
*   **Spacebar:** Hard Drop (Instant lock)
